Safin in No Time to Die. Plan: Kill all the bad guys and then use magic robots to...get rich? I think. Honestly can't figure it out. 2/10 for incomprehensibility.
Blofeld in Spectre. Plan: Control all world intelligence. There's already something who does that, it's called Google. Just buy Google. 3/10.
Silva in Skyfall. Plan: Kill M. Simple, clean, elaborately executed but since it's the only Bond villain plan that actually works, hard to argue with. 9/10.
Greene in Quantum of Solace. Plan: take over Bolivia to gain control of its resources. Mate, Gina Rinehart did this in Australia and Bolivia would be way easier, all you need is a TV station. 2/10.

Le Chiffre in Casino Royale. Plan: Win a card game to pay off money he pinched. Very poor plan in all respects which anyone could tell him, and could have easily been avoided by not pinching the money.  1/10
Colonel Moon in Die Another Day. Plan: Conquer South Korea with a space laser and then the world. I think. Again seems to miss the 'if WW3 starts you'll be dead' thing. 2/10.
Elektra in the World Is Not Enough. Gain control of Russian oil by blowing up Istanbul. Solid plan given how the world works, extra points for girlbossing right up close to the sun. 7/10.

Carver in Tomorrow Never Dies. Plan: Blow up the Chinese government and stage a coup to get broadcasting rights. Has an iPad in 1997, doesn't think to get rich off that instead. Elaborate and stupid, as well as unnecessary. 1/10
Trevallyn in GoldenEye. Plan: nuke London with an EMP moments after robbing the Bank of England to cripple the UK and get rich. Again, not seeing any real drawbacks and no real harm done, so 9/10.
Sanchez in Licence to Kill. No plan at all other than "be a drug dealer". Hard to rate so just going with 5.5/10 as an average.
Koskov in The Living Daylights. Plan: Have MI6 kill the head of the KGB and then buy arms from the Taliban. Have seen this film a bunch of times, still don't understand it. 3/10 just for complexity.

Zorin in A View to a Kill. Plan: Destroy Silicon Valley to gain control of microchip market. Problem is: all the people who need microchips are in Silicon Valley. Stupid plan but if it worked, would have destroyed Silicon Valley which has few drawbacks. 5/10
Orlov in Octopussy: Start WW3. Again, buddy, if there's a nuclear war you'll be dead after it so...1/10
Kristatos in For Your Eyes Only. Plan: give a British navy code device to the Soviets so the Royal Navy is a bit less good. No actual problems caused by the plan but beneficial to himself. 9/10
Drax in Moonraker. Plan: Exactly the same as Stromberg but the new civilisation is in space. Rating it 1/10 because what the fuck
Stromberg in The Spy Who Loved Me. Plan: destroy the world and start a new civilisation under the sea. I'm going to rate this 2/10 for the sole reason it's fuckin stupid.

Scaramanga in The Man With the Golden Gun. Plan: Sell a solar energy device to the highest bidder. Just ordinary capitalism really, and surprisingly prescient. Really not that bad a guy other than the murders. 8/10

Kananga in Live and Let Die.  Plan: Become a very powerful drug lord as well as president of his own country. Hard to fault, really, although probably too simple because it's not hard to figure out who's behind all these drugs from one single country. 6/10

Blofeld again in Diamonds Are Forever. Plan: gain monopoly on nuclear control and sell to highest bidder. Uses some kind of satellite or something, very elaborate because it's an indecipherable plan. 4/10.

Blofeld in On Her Majesty's Secret Service: Blackmail the world to give him a French noble title, using hypnotised women and a crop virus. Or you could just bribe the French government with all that money you seem to have. 2/10.
Blofeld in You Only Live Twice. Plan: Start World War III. World War III will kill you as well, Ernst, not a great plan. Falls down through elaborate plan involving spaceships. 3/10
Largo/Blofeld in Thunderball. Plan: blow up Miami unless paid billions of dollars. Poor plan because nobody would give a shit about Miami. 4/10.
Goldfinger in Goldfinger. Plan: Irradiate the gold at Fort Knox and increase his own wealth. Pretty good plan, would have worked if not for the fact Fort Knox doesn't work like that. 7.5/10
Kronstein/Klebb in From Russia With Love. Plan: Kill James Bond. Simple, clear objective, execution too elaborate as it involved more than just shooting him on the loo. 6/10
